{"DECK":[{"def":"To cover; to overspread.","pos":""},{"def":"To dress, as the person; to clothe; especially, to clothe with more than ordinary elegance; to array; to adorn; to embellish.","pos":""}],"DECKER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, decks or adorns; a coverer; as, a table decker.","pos":""},{"def":"A vessel which has a deck or decks; -- used esp.","pos":""}],"DECKLE":[{"def":"A separate thin wooden frame used to form the border of a hand mold, or a curb of India rubber or other material which rests on, and forms the edge of, the mold in a paper machine and determines the width of the paper.","pos":""}],"DECKLE EDGE":[{"def":"The rough, untrimmed edge of paper left by the deckle; also, a rough edge in imitation of this.","pos":""}],"DECKLE-EDGED":[{"def":"Having a deckle edge; as, deckle-edged paper; a deckle-edged book.","pos":""}]}